<node><name>Review Information</name>
<id>3</id>
<lefticon>solo</lefticon>
<righticon>reading</righticon>
<column>OOC</column>
<textHTML>&lt;p&gt;Students do a reading about gender roles, establishing diﬀerences between gender and sex and how they are constructed. Students also review statistics regarding occupational segregation to prepare for the activity.&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>100</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
<tagARRAY/>
</node>
<node><name>Assign Group Work</name>
<id>4</id>
<lefticon>undefined</lefticon>
<righticon>orchestration</righticon>
<column>ICI</column>
<textHTML>&lt;p&gt;The instructor separates the class into groups of 4-6 and asks them to list 6 characteristics associated with each of the jobs identiﬁed on the whiteboard (nurse, engineer, teacher, lawyer, manager, and ﬂight attendant).&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>100</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
<tagARRAY/>
</node>
<node><name>Analyze Assigned Content</name>
<id>5</id>
<lefticon>group</lefticon>
<righticon>problem</righticon>
<column>ICS</column>
<textHTML>&lt;p&gt;Students explore and question the stereotypes generally associated with each job in their groups when coming up with their 6 characteristics.&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>100</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
<tagARRAY/>
</node>
<node><name>Discuss Assigned Content</name>
<id>6</id>
<lefticon>group</lefticon>
<righticon>discuss</righticon>
<column>ICS</column>
<textHTML>&lt;p&gt;Students then discuss characteristics and qualiﬁcations associated with each job as well as what qualiﬁes a person as being competent in the profession.&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>100</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
<tagARRAY/>
</node>
